<p>Good edits, especially the hook; it's now an actual hook.</p>
<p>1) Disappearances could work. At the very least, it eliminates a connection being made. However, as much as I hate saying it, the tree does need some protein; if it's just making people suffer that weakens it.</p>
<p>2) You've already established that the tree controls the kids and counselors, so making them do minor things like framing another camper works. it also keeps to the theme.</p>
<p>3) You need to actually say it; it's a rare bit of humor, and you need it. It's also a neat subversion of how shameful self-urination is.</p>
<p>4) Cool.</p>
<p>5) The origins of the weakness helps to clarify things. Also, if it's a weakness, then it helps explain how they found it.</p>

