<p>So my biggest concern is this part:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Many of these children later runaway from home, but some of them return to the tree, carve their name in its trunk and kill themselves.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><em>My concern is two-fold:</em><br />
<strong>a)</strong> using suicide (especially of children!) as shock value in a skip is so grim dark edgy that I lose interest immediately&#8230; using suicide in a skip needs to be handled delicately, and earning that edgy subject matter with some of substance. Here it feels unearned<br />
<strong>b)</strong> the thing what which makes you crazy, and/or kill yourself, is such an overwrought trope on the wiki that I just tend to lose interest. The thing making you crazy/kill yourself really has to say something interesting/new or it’ll just feel cliched. I don’t see much here to suggest you’re pushing through the usual tropes of using such a compulsion effect on an anomaly.</p>

